      "As you can see, areas with colors closer to red, or dark red are more susceptible to experiencing a crime and this is the basis on which we can alert personell about dangerous areas, for future prospect, we aim to achieve a more accurate version of this model and the same for smaller scales, such as district-wise, city-wise, and hopefully as per smaller areas and locations as well. the results shown above are on basis of actual crime reports and a sentiment value that has been generated at random. yo can put your own set of tweets and create a csv file which will perform the same operation. The basis of judgement for the output is crime rate multiplied by negative % of tweets/positive % of tweets\n"
